18/03/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- EU Commissioner for Enlargement Olli Rehn makes his first visit to Bulgaria on Friday (18 March).
He will meet with President Georgi Parvanov, Parliament Speaker Borislav Velikov, Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg and Foreign Minister Solomon Passy.
Rehn will also address parliament.
His main focus during the trip will be Bulgaria's remaining commitments and preparations -- particularly judicial and administrative reforms -- in the 21 months prior to its target date for EU accession.
(News.bg, Novinite - 18/03/05)
